what is the 2 bet system? how does it work

Good question 👍 — the 2-bet system is one of the key features in crash games like Aviator. It lets a player place two separate bets in the same round, each behaving independently.

🔴 What is the 2 Bet System?

Instead of placing only 1 bet per round, the player can place:

Bet A (e.g., $10)

Bet B (e.g., $20)

Both bets run in the same round, but:

Each has its own cashout

Each can have different strategy

⚙️ How it works (simple example)
Player sets:

Bet A = 10 (Auto cashout at 1.50x)

Bet B = 10 (No auto, manual cashout)

Round starts:

Multiplier grows:

1.00 → 1.20 → 1.50 → 2.00 → 3.00 → CRASH

What happens:
✅ Bet A (safe strategy)

Auto cashout at 1.50x

Wins: 10 × 1.50 = 15

Profit: +5

⚠️ Bet B (risky strategy)

Player waits longer

Suppose crash happens at 3.00x

If player cashed at 2.50x:

Wins: 10 × 2.50 = 25

If player didn’t click:

❌ loses full 10

🧠 Why 2 bets exist (strategy)

Players use 2 bets to balance risk:

🟢 Strategy 1 — Safe + Risk

Bet A → low auto (1.5x) → small but frequent wins

Bet B → high target (3x–10x) → big profit chance

🟡 Strategy 2 — Both different autos

Bet A → 1.3x

Bet B → 2.0x

🔴 Strategy 3 — Full gamble

Both bets no auto → manual cashout

💡 Important rules

Both bets use the same crash point

If crash = 2.00x:

any bet cashed before 2.00 → win

any bet still active → lose

